  "response": "The length of time marijuana (THC) stays detectable in blood depends on several factors:\n\n1. Occasional users:\n- Usually 1-2 days after use\n- Potentially up to 7 days\n\n2. Regular/heavy users:\n- Can be detectable for 7-30 days after last use\n- Chronic heavy users may test positive for over 30 days\n\nFactors affecting detection time:\n- Frequency of use\n- Dosage\n- Metabolism\n- Body fat percentage\n- Hydration levels\n\nDifferent drug tests have varying detection windows:\n- Blood tests: 1-2 days (occasional users)\n- Urine tests: 3-30 days\n- Hair tests: Up to 90 days\n- Saliva tests: 24-72 hours\n\nThese are general guidelines, and individual results can vary.",
